-- Russia Allows Beef From Cargill Plant in Canada, Ministry Says
-- B y   W h i t n e y   M c F e r r o n
-- 2011-02-04T20:38:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-04/russia-allows-beef-from-cargill-plant-in-canada-ministry-says.html
  Russia  has agreed to allow beef
imports from a Cargill Meat Solutions plant in Guelph, Ontario,
Agriculture and Agri-Food Canada said.  The deal may lead to an additional C$2 million in annual
sales for Cargill, according to the e-mailed statement. Canadian
beef exports to Russia were worth more than C$20 million last
year, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Whitney McFerron in Chicago at 
 wmcferron1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
